# SPECTRAL PCM — Research Methodology

## Purpose
Every phase research file feeds directly into course content. The quality of the research determines whether a Boeing Defence analyst, Thales engineer, or SOCOMD operator finds this credible. Hold every claim to that standard.

## Source Hierarchy (descending authority)

| Tier | Source Type | Examples | Confidence |
|---|---|---|---|
| T1 | Official government / military publication | DoD Budget docs, USAF fact sheets, ADF capability releases, parliamentary defence committee reports | HIGH |
| T2 | Verified defence journalism / specialist press | Jane's Defence Weekly, Defence News, Breaking Defense, The War Zone, Aviation Week | HIGH |
| T3 | Manufacturer / prime contractor releases | Datasheets, press releases, trade show presentations | MEDIUM — flag marketing inflation |
| T4 | Academic / think tank analysis | RAND, IISS, RUSI, CSIS, ASPI | MEDIUM — analysis, not primary data |
| T5 | Verified open-source field reporting | Oryx (equipment losses), UA Weapons Tracker, verified social media with corroboration | MEDIUM — flag if single-source |
| T6 | Unverified / single-source reporting | Anonymous claims, single social media post, unconfirmed | LOW — include only if operationally significant, flag clearly |

## Confidence Flagging (use in every platform entry)

```
✅ CONFIRMED — T1 or T2 source, cross-referenced
⚠️ ESTIMATED — manufacturer claim or analyst estimate, not independently verified
❓ UNCONFIRMED — single source, significant uncertainty
🔒 CLASSIFIED LIKELY — capability exists but parameters not public; do not speculate on classified figures
```

