## What Every Research File Must Contain

1. **Platform specs to Jane's standard** — MTOW, endurance, ceiling, payload, datalink type, frequency band, guidance mode, warhead (if applicable), unit cost (if OSINT-available)
2. **Operational employment context** — how it is actually used, not just what it can do on paper
3. **Defeat mechanism** — every capability section must include how to counter it
4. **Conflict evidence** — named engagement, named conflict, approximate date. "Used in Ukraine" is not enough. "Lancet-3 strikes on Ukrainian M109 SPH at Zaporizhzhia front, Sep–Dec 2023, documented by Oryx and field video" is.
5. **The "so what"** — every section ends with what this means for the student in their job

## What to Avoid

- Copying manufacturer datasheets without operational context
- Stating estimated performance as confirmed fact
- Ignoring the countermeasure — every capability has a defeat mechanism
- Describing what a system *can* do without saying what it *actually did* in combat
- Padding with background history that doesn't change the operational picture

## Research Scope by Phase

### Phase 3 — Loitering Munitions & OWA
Cover: Shahed-136/Geran-2 (variants, production volume, defeat rate economics), Lancet-1/3, KUB-BLA, Switchblade 300/600, Phoenix Ghost, Hero series (Hero-30/120/400), WB Warmate, Harop, Harpy, Rotem L. Focus: unit cost vs intercept cost, employment TTPs, signature reduction, swarm employment.

### Phase 4 — C-UAS Taxonomy
Cover: Detect (RF detection, radar, EO/IR, acoustic), Decide (classification AI, ROE constraints), Defeat (RF jamming, kinetic interceptors, DEW, net/physical). Systems: Drone Dome, Coyote Block 3, SHORAD integration, DroneShield, SMASH 2000, Skyranger 30. Focus: layered defence, magazine depth problem, cost exchange ratio.

### Phase 5 — Emerging Tech Horizon
Cover: AI/autonomy in terminal guidance (removing RF link = jamming-immune), swarm coordination protocols, MUM-T (AH-64E/MQ-1C), Collaborative Combat Aircraft (Ghost Bat, XQ-58, FCAS NGAD), directed energy maturity (HELIOS, IRON BEAM, DragonFire). Focus: 3–5 year horizon, what changes the tactical equation.

### Phase 6 — Doctrine & TTPs by Nation
Cover: Russia (attrition OWA model, electronic warfare integration), Ukraine (FPV saturation + rapid innovation cycle, DELTA system), Israel (precision + persistence, Harop SEAD), Turkey (TB2 export model + doctrine package), Iran (proxy swarm employment, Shahed export), China (A2/AD integration, GJ-11 stealth UCAV, swarm doctrine). Include: Nagorno-Karabakh 2020, Libya 2019–2020, Ukraine 2022–2026, Red Sea 2023–2025, India-Pakistan 2025.
